processes.name: doElasticSearch
processes.description:
ElasticSearch plugin is used to search log analytics, full-text search, security intelligence, business analytics, and operational intelligence use cases.

Elasticsearch is a distributed, RESTful search and analytics engine.

processes.name: cleanSearchDir
processes.description: This plugin is used to clean the search directory to remove any previous result.

processes.name: createSearchDir
processes.description: createSearchDir plugin is used for creating search directory.

processes.name: convertObj2File
processes.description: The convertObj2File plugin converts the search  results from the previous step into string and stores into file.

processes.name: listFile
processes.description: The listFile plugin gets the name of the latest file created.

processes.name: copySearchResults2AWS
processes.description: The copySearchResults2AWS plugin uploads the file in AWS S3 bucket.

exportedPipeline.description:
gasdhoijdCopy Elastic Results to S3 template:
Usage: This template can be used to copy ElasticSearch query results to AWS S3 bucket.
Prerequisites: 1) ElasticSearch instance should be available for searching the result.
                         2) AWS S3 bucket should be created to copy the data.
